description:
The first city across the River Jordan was Jericho and the story of its miraculous defeat is one that can only be attributed to the power of God. Before crossing the river, Moses laid his hands on Joshua and set him apart as leader of the Israelites. Although Jericho was a formidable city by the standards of their day, when the people relied on the power of God, he removed the obstacles in their path.
